1
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:13,567
<i>You're probably convinced now
that I had nothing to do</i>

2
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:15,600
<i>with all the things
they're saying.</i>

3
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:17,167
<i>You two had better
watch yourselves.</i>

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,433
<i> You'll both rot in jail.</i>

5
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> Jeff, call your mom.</i>

6
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,700
<i>What was the good news
again, son?</i>

7
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,533
<i>Mom, we already brought
Dad home.</i>

8
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:29,400
<i>Really?
How did that happen?</i>

9
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,333
<i> Manuel, the dessert...</i>

10
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> Where are you?</i>

11
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:35,700
<i> Manuel!</i>

12
00:00:35,833 --> 00:00:37,167
<i>- What's your problem?
- Open the gate!</i>

13
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:38,833
<i> You've got some nerve!</i>

14
00:00:38,967 --> 00:00:41,267
<i> You're not allowed here!</i>

15
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,133
<i> Hey!</i>

16
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,467
Manuel!

17
00:00:47,833 --> 00:00:51,233
- Manuel!
- Don't hurt my father!

18
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,800
Stay out of this.

19
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,800
I'm talking to my husband!

20
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:58,133
What happened, Manuel?

21
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:00,767
Didn't we have an agreement?

22
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,433
I did everything to keep it.

23
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:06,367
I spent a lot of money.

24
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:08,033
I swallowed my pride.

25
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,900
I made sacrifices.

26
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:12,400
I even gave up justice
for Jessica.

27
00:01:12,533 --> 00:01:14,067
For what?

28
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,533
So you could leave me again?

29
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:18,700
Now that Coleen is free, what?

30
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,133
You're running away from me?

31
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:23,000
Hazel, I already know the truth.

32
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:27,500
Don't pretend
you're so clean and innocent.

33
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,067
Didang, call the guards.

34
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,467
Okay, I will.

35
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:35,000
What are you talking about?

36
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:37,767
My suspicion
from the very beginning.

37
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:40,767
Timo had already spoken, Hazel.

38
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:45,233
He said he never actually saw
Coleen and Jessica fighting.

39
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:48,467
You paid him to say Coleen
pushed her sister.

40
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:52,767
And when you had the chance
to take Dad back,

41
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:55,200
you used Timo again.

42
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:58,867
You paid him to retract
his statement.

43
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,100
And that wasn't enough.

44
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:03,633
You even threatened his family.

45
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:05,267
You're so evil.

46
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,567
No, you are.

47
00:02:08,633 --> 00:02:10,067
You're the evil ones!

48
00:02:11,067 --> 00:02:13,067
You made up stories

49
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,667
just so Manuel
would come back to you!

50
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:16,467
Made up?

51
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:19,967
Here, receipt.

52
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,033
Oh!

53
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,067
A copy of Timo's letter.

54
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:46,900
It clearly says you threatened
to hurt him and his family.

55
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,833
That's why he confessed to us.

56
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,133
Go on, deny it.

57
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:03,233
Please have a seat.

58
00:03:04,067 --> 00:03:05,467
Cousin.

59
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:08,700
Stay there, Felma.

60
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,700
Cousin...

61
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,833
how are the results?

62
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:36,400
Well...

63
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:40,667
Based on the MRI results emailed
to us for Miss Felma...

64
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,633
Dr. Dionela's initial
diagnosis is confirmed.

65
00:03:46,900 --> 00:03:53,333
Meningioma of the frontal lobe
of the brain or a brain tumor.

66
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:02,933
Doctor...

67
00:04:07,367 --> 00:04:09,033
Is it malignant?

68
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:16,000
Does it spread, Doctor?

69
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:28,400
So what is this now?

70
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:31,067
What is this? Huh?

71
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,233
How do I know you didn't write
that yourselves?

72
00:04:33,367 --> 00:04:35,000
Anyone can copy his handwriting!

73
00:04:35,133 --> 00:04:37,200
You're probably behind this!

74
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,233
Then let's go!

75
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:40,467
Let's go to the police station
right now!

76
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,567
You face Timo!

77
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:43,067
Let him tell you
the truth himself.

78
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,867
And if that's still not enough,

79
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,600
should we also call his wife
and mother?

80
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:50,033
How about your two men
we caught in the act?

81
00:04:50,167 --> 00:04:52,433
Hazel, I've been watching you
for a long time.

82
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,467
Your strange behavior,

83
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,800
your secret phone calls...

84
00:05:00,433 --> 00:05:01,900
<i> I'll give it to you.</i>

85
00:05:02,067 --> 00:05:04,133
<i>But honestly,
I don't even have to.</i>

86
00:05:04,267 --> 00:05:05,667
<i> I already got what I wanted.</i>

87
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,133
<i>Timo already did everything
I told him to do.</i>

88
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:10,367
Hazel, I'm not stupid enough

89
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,333
to believe you're not
hiding anything.

90
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,600
Go on.

91
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,167
Let's say it's true.

92
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:21,267
So what now?

93
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:22,967
What are you going to do?

94
00:05:24,067 --> 00:05:25,133
Sue me?

95
00:05:25,267 --> 00:05:26,433
Throw me in jail?

96
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:29,900
I told you before, Manuel,
didn't I?

97
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:33,533
I'll do anything to get justice

98
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:34,567
for my child's death.

99
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:36,000
Didn't I tell you that?

100
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,633
But lying?

101
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:39,000
Hurting other people?

102
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:42,300
Hazel, what kind of person
are you?

103
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:43,833
Do you even have a conscience?

104
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:47,100
Darn you!
Darn you, Manuel!

105
00:05:47,233 --> 00:05:50,300
I already told you not to hurt
my father!

106
00:05:51,767 --> 00:05:53,533
You know what?
You're so selfish.

107
00:05:54,533 --> 00:05:56,900
This isn't about Jessica.

108
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:59,767
This is about you.

109
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,533
Then what?

110
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:04,133
You wanted to take Dad
away from us,

111
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:05,633
so you manipulated him?

112
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:09,900
Well, we won't allow it anymore,
he belongs with us.

113
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,567
Manuel is mine.

114
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,833
He's my husband!

115
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:19,133
Then, we're his children.

116
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:21,667
So our father belongs with us!

117
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,533
- Stop it, stop it!
- Hazel!

118
00:06:23,667 --> 00:06:25,833
Stop it!

119
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:02,333
Manuel.

120
00:07:03,867 --> 00:07:05,500
You can stand now.

121
00:07:06,933 --> 00:07:08,400
You're standing.

122
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:10,767
So that means...

123
00:07:12,167 --> 00:07:14,233
the therapy worked?

124
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:18,033
Would I waste my time on it
if it didn't?

125
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:22,433
Hazel, I've hidden it from you
for a long time.

126
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:27,933
But I followed everything Dr.
Tamayo told me to do.

127
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:36,933
Little by little,

128
00:07:37,067 --> 00:07:39,467
by God's grace,
I was able to stand.

129
00:07:56,967 --> 00:07:58,533
And now I can walk.

130
00:08:50,367 --> 00:08:51,733
<i> Weren't...</i>

131
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,767
<i>you already lying down
before I stepped out?</i>

132
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:58,667
<i> I just went to pee, Hazel.</i>

133
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,167
<i> How did you...</i>

134
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,333
<i> get into your wheelchair?</i>

135
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,733
So that's why...

136
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,500
That's why...

137
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:15,300
that day, I wondered how you got
back into your wheelchair.

138
00:09:16,467 --> 00:09:19,233
So that's why, because you can
already walk, Manuel.

139
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,767
You didn't even notice, did you?

140
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:27,500
Because you only think
about yourself!

141
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,733
So now what? Huh?

142
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:33,533
I can stand now, Hazel,
I can walk now.

143
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:37,567
I can fight you now.

144
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,367
And I'm telling you.

145
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:42,100
You will never hurt my children!

146
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,267
Doctor...

147
00:09:50,433 --> 00:09:53,133
what stage is the tumor?

148
00:09:56,267 --> 00:09:58,367
Has it already spread to...

149
00:09:59,567 --> 00:10:01,467
other parts of my body?

150
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:02,700
Felma.

151
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:07,333
Based on the size of the tumor,

152
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:08,700
it could be malignant.

153
00:10:08,833 --> 00:10:10,900
But it's also possible
that it isn't.

154
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:14,067
The only way we can confirm
is through biopsy.

155
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:20,867
So I need surgery?

156
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,633
Yes, Miss Felma.

157
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:26,167
It will also help relieve
the pain and the symptoms

158
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,833
you've been experiencing.

159
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:31,000
This tumor is causing
intracranial pressure.

160
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:33,633
A pressure inside your skull.

161
00:10:33,767 --> 00:10:37,367
That's why you often have
headaches and feel dizzy.

162
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,433
Doctor, what if...

163
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:43,500
I don't go through
with the surgery?

164
00:10:44,867 --> 00:10:49,033
Miss Felma, the symptoms
could get worse.

165
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:52,333
Aside from headaches
and dizziness,

166
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,533
it can also affect
your vision...

167
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,633
mobility...

168
00:10:57,767 --> 00:11:02,233
behavior, mood,
or even your personality.

169
00:11:04,533 --> 00:11:05,500
Cousin...

170
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,700
Felma has already been showing
behavioral changes.

171
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:12,700
<i> Book me a ticket.</i>

172
00:11:12,833 --> 00:11:14,700
<i>I'll go with you to Davao later.</i>

173
00:11:16,267 --> 00:11:18,067
That was impulsive of you.

174
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,833
You weren't like that before.

175
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,467
Even Jeffrey...

176
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:29,400
told me you've been
getting forgetful.

177
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:33,667
They invited you to visit
Jessica's grave...

178
00:11:34,667 --> 00:11:36,033
but you said
you couldn't remember.

179
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:41,000
And you've been eating food
you never used to like.

180
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:45,167
- Ah...
- I don't remember.

181
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,967
Cousin...

182
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:48,800
if Felma undergoes surgery...

183
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,267
she'll get better
right away, right?

184
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:56,233
The symptoms will go away,
and there's a good chance

185
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:58,967
the tumor won't come back?

186
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:03,000
I can't guarantee
anything, cousin.

187
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:05,100
But one thing's for sure.

188
00:12:05,233 --> 00:12:07,933
Once we biopsy the tumor,

189
00:12:08,067 --> 00:12:10,533
we can work on
a treatment modality,

190
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:12,800
specific to her case.

191
00:12:12,933 --> 00:12:16,467
It could be chemotherapy
or radiation.

192
00:12:16,633 --> 00:12:18,700
That is, if the tumor turns out
to be cancerous.

193
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:23,600
So I still won't be
completely cured.

194
00:12:35,667 --> 00:12:37,167
Felma.

195
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,500
What are you still waiting for?

196
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:40,633
Leave!

197
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:43,700
Manuel, don't do this.

198
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:45,167
Wait, let's talk first.

199
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,167
Don't make me leave.

200
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:48,067
There's nothing left
to talk about.

201
00:12:48,233 --> 00:12:50,600
I will never get back together
with you.

202
00:12:50,733 --> 00:12:52,400
What about our agreement?

203
00:12:52,533 --> 00:12:53,500
We had an agreement, didn't we?

204
00:12:53,633 --> 00:12:55,733
Hazel, that agreement means
nothing now.

205
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:57,567
Don't you think at all?

206
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,167
Didn't you hear everything
we said?

207
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:02,000
I know all your lies now.

208
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:03,167
So from the very beginning,

209
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:05,033
that agreement
was already pointless

210
00:13:05,167 --> 00:13:06,533
because Coleen was innocent!

211
00:13:06,667 --> 00:13:08,267
No. She's not
completely innocent.

212
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,600
If she hadn't fought with
Jessica outside the hospital,

213
00:13:10,733 --> 00:13:11,567
maybe she wouldn't
have been hit.

214
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:12,833
Maybe our child
would still be alive.

215
00:13:12,967 --> 00:13:15,267
Hazel, we're just going
in circles!

216
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,533
- Manuel, please.
- Leave!

217
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:18,900
Don't do this, Manuel,
have mercy.

218
00:13:19,033 --> 00:13:20,400
You're all I have left.

219
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:22,367
Jessica is gone.

220
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:25,600
I'm all alone now, Manuel,
please don't...

221
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:27,733
Please have mercy on me, Manuel.

222
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:29,533
- Hazel.
- You're all I have, please.

223
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:31,600
Manuel, I love you so much.

224
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:34,600
- Manuel, I love you.
- Hazel, that's not love!

225
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:37,600
Real love means sacrifice.

226
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:40,067
It does everything
for the person you love.

227
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,900
And you, what did you sacrifice?

228
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:44,500
Nothing, Hazel.

229
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:47,467
Jessica has been gone
for a long time,

230
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,500
yet you're still using her.

231
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,400
You're a terrible person!

232
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,033
Don't do this to me, Manuel.

233
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,500
- Don't...
- Go, leave, Hazel.

234
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:56,733
- How...
- Go!

235
00:13:56,867 --> 00:13:58,400
- Wait!
- Stop harassing

236
00:13:58,533 --> 00:14:00,833
- my family and me! Go!
- He's all I have left!

237
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:02,233
Hazel, leave!

238
00:14:02,367 --> 00:14:03,767
- He's the only one I have!
- Leave, Hazel!

239
00:14:03,900 --> 00:14:05,533
He's all I have left!

240
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:07,233
- Have mercy, just a moment!
- Hazel, leave!

241
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:08,300
- Wait! Manuel!
- Go!

242
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:09,700
Wait, don't do this, Manuel!

243
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,733
- Leave!
- Manuel! Manuel, wait!

244
00:14:11,867 --> 00:14:13,867
- Wait, Manuel, don't do this!
- Go! Leave!

245
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,100
Wait!

246
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:16,933
Wait, Manuel!

247
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:19,267
Manuel, open the door!

248
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,433
Manuel! Open this!

249
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:25,400
Manuel!

250
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:29,000
Manuel, you're all I have.

251
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:32,300
Manuel, please.
Please have mercy on me.

252
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,067
Manuel!

253
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,933
Please have mercy on me!

254
00:14:38,067 --> 00:14:40,333
Manuel! Manuel!

255
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:43,333
Manuel! Manuel!

256
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:46,067
Please, I'm begging you.

257
00:15:03,367 --> 00:15:04,600
Felma...

258
00:15:05,867 --> 00:15:09,900
about what Emil said regarding
your condition...

259
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,000
Noah...

260
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:16,433
I'd like to rest now.

261
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:20,567
I understand.

262
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:22,367
It has been a long day.

263
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:26,300
Miss Felma, if you like,

264
00:15:26,433 --> 00:15:29,700
I can help you arrange your
clothes in the cabinet.

265
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:32,733
Ah, I can do it myself.

266
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:34,500
Thank you very much.

267
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:37,367
- Good night.
- Good night.

268
00:15:39,933 --> 00:15:41,367
See you tomorrow.

269
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:50,667
I know that sigh.

270
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:54,333
Aren't you happy
being with Felma?

271
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:04,367
I am happy, Manang Lucy.

272
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:09,800
But there's also sadness
because she's sick.

273
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:12,367
God is merciful.

274
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:14,600
Nothing is impossible for Him.

275
00:16:14,733 --> 00:16:18,367
If it's His will
to heal Felma...

276
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:23,300
He can do it,
so let's pray harder, okay?

277
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,267
Ma'am, I really want her
to get better.

278
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:31,300
I want the best for her.

279
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,933
You're worthless, Manuel.

280
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:53,867
After everything...

281
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,600
I gave you everything.

282
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:06,100
I did everything for you.

283
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,167
And then...

284
00:17:11,267 --> 00:17:13,633
this is all you do in return?

285
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:46,767
You bastard!

286
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:50,267
- Ah... Ah...
- Friend?

287
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:52,933
Friend!

288
00:17:54,167 --> 00:17:57,067
What's happening to you now?

289
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:10,467
Wait a second.

290
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,400
I'll just get something
to clean this up.

291
00:18:25,967 --> 00:18:27,767
Dad, be careful.

292
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:31,733
Sir, since you can walk now,

293
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,867
we got you a fresh bed sheet.

294
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,800
Thank you.

295
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:43,133
Dad, you didn't tell us

296
00:18:43,267 --> 00:18:45,500
you could already walk.

297
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:49,000
It's because I wanted
to surprise you.

298
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:52,500
Now we can party again!

299
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:54,567
- Let's party!
- Party!

300
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,867
- Ah!
- That's right!

301
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:57,867
Let's do that on my birthday.

302
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,167
We'll dance hip-hop, like this.

303
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,200
- Oh, oh, oh, oh...
- Not like that.

304
00:19:02,333 --> 00:19:04,067
You're so silly.

305
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,267
I can't do that yet.

306
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,667
My legs are still weak.

307
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:10,900
That's why I still need
to continue therapy.

308
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:13,033
So we're not packing
that up yet, Dad?

309
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:14,833
No, you can put it away.

310
00:19:14,967 --> 00:19:17,433
It's good that
I'm walking around anyway.

311
00:19:17,567 --> 00:19:20,000
It's exercise, too, right?

312
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:23,167
Dad...

313
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:29,233
I wish Jessica could
see you now, walking like this.

314
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:33,067
She can see it.

315
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,467
I hope your mom comes home soon.

316
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:39,667
She'd be so happy to see this.

317
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,300
You know, you're really
the reason

318
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:44,567
I pushed myself to walk again.

319
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:02,833
Oh my god! No!

320
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,533
Let go of me, Alice!

321
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,633
- Hazel!
- Let go of me!

322
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:22,700
Really?

323
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,100
You're going to hurt yourself?

324
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,300
What is the problem, Hazel?

325
00:20:28,433 --> 00:20:30,000
Where's Manuel?

326
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:33,267
He's gone, Alice.

327
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:37,100
Manuel is gone.

328
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,867
He went back
to his illegitimate family.

329
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:44,067
What?

330
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:48,267
He knows the truth now.

331
00:20:51,533 --> 00:20:58,633
He knows I paid Timo
to frame Coleen.

332
00:21:00,333 --> 00:21:05,367
He also knows the threats
I made to Diana.

333
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:07,733
Everything.

334
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,400
He knows everything.

335
00:21:14,233 --> 00:21:15,800
He left me.

336
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:19,233
And guess what?

337
00:21:23,167 --> 00:21:25,100
He can walk now.

338
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:29,800
So the therapy worked?

339
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:32,533
Obviously.

340
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:36,033
But he didn't tell you.

341
00:21:37,367 --> 00:21:39,233
That bastard is clever.

342
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:42,667
All this time...

343
00:21:44,433 --> 00:21:47,533
he was watching my every move.

344
00:21:47,667 --> 00:21:49,967
<i> I have no one left to turn to.</i>

345
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:52,300
<i>You already discussed this
with Diana</i>

346
00:21:52,433 --> 00:21:54,200
<i> and Timo, didn't you?</i>

347
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:56,733
<i> Then wait.</i>

348
00:21:56,867 --> 00:22:01,933
I was so stupid to think
he wasn't smart.

349
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:04,733
But why is it like this, Alice?

350
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,833
Even after he made
a fool out of me...

351
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:13,667
I still love him.

352
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:17,367
I still love him.

353
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:19,100
I still love Manuel.

354
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,533
I can't do this.

355
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:24,667
I can't live without him.

356
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:29,633
Only he and Jessica ever
accepted me, Alice.

357
00:22:33,667 --> 00:22:36,000
I want my husband back.

358
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:39,333
I want Manuel back.

359
00:22:39,467 --> 00:22:41,467
I want Manuel back.

360
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:44,167
I want him back.

361
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:48,233
Alice, I want him back.

362
00:22:53,433 --> 00:22:59,000
Dear God,
I don't even know...

363
00:23:01,767 --> 00:23:03,900
what I should be praying for.

364
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:09,800
No matter how much
I prepare myself...

365
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:13,533
for life's trials...

366
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:21,933
it's still shocking
to get sick like this.

367
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:33,567
Lord, please give me strength
and a clear mind.

368
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,800
Please help me, Lord.

369
00:23:40,767 --> 00:23:42,667
Heal me.

370
00:23:44,067 --> 00:23:47,667
Heal me for my family.

371
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:51,533
Please help me.

372
00:23:59,033 --> 00:24:00,033
Manuel?

373
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:02,133
Thank goodness you're back.

374
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:03,600
I was actually going
to surprise you,

375
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:05,267
<i> but you weren't here.</i>

376
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:07,767
<i> Paz is calling me, Manuel.</i>

377
00:24:07,900 --> 00:24:09,467
She says the conference
is about to start.

378
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,767
Think of a way for me to get

379
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:13,833
- my husband back.
- Hazel, you've done everything.

380
00:24:13,967 --> 00:24:16,233
You played the villain,
you played the saint.

381
00:24:16,367 --> 00:24:18,267
You were even one step away
from hurting yourself.

382
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:21,533
You're right,
If they see me helpless,

383
00:24:21,667 --> 00:24:24,033
especially Manuel,
he'll come back to me.

384
00:24:24,167 --> 00:24:25,800
If you don't want them to worry,

385
00:24:25,933 --> 00:24:27,367
shouldn't you be getting
the surgery?

386
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:28,800
I've made up my mind.

387
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:30,600
I'm not having the operation.

388
00:24:30,733 --> 00:24:31,867
Didang!

389
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,500
- Miss Paz! Oh my!
- Hey, man!

390
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:37,100
Weren't you and Felma supposed
to have a conference

391
00:24:37,233 --> 00:24:38,267
in Batangas?

392
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:41,067
Conference? Batangas?
What are you talking about?
